        public static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_SUFFIX
        Defines the suffix that is used to build the URL (without '.json' extension). OSGi service property. This property is mandatory.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PROPERTY_SUFFIX_PATTERN

        public static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_SUFFIX_PATTERN
        Defining a regular pattern to match the URL suffix (without '.json' extension). If not set, an exact match with the suffix is enforced. This allows processors to produce "variable" output based on additional suffix information passed after the main suffix part. OSGi service property.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PROPERTY_ENABLED

        public static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_ENABLED
        A processor is enabled by default. If an "enabled" property exists, and is set to false, the processor is disabled. OSGi service property.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
